  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink299-kilavi">iyaṟkaippuṇarcci puṇarntu nīṅkiya nilaimaikkaṇ talaimakaḷ āyaveḷḷattōṭu kūṭi niṟkak kaṇṭa talaimakaṉ makiḻnta vuḷḷattaṉāyt taṉṉuḷḷē colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en"> 
          What the hero, having become inwardly delighted, said to himself when he saw the heroine—after they had united in natural union and parted—standing together with her large group of companions.        
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink299">
<l>kuṉṟa nāṭaṉ kuṉṟattuk kavāaṟ</l>
<l>paiñcuṉaip pūtta pakuvāyk kuvaḷaiyu</l>
<l>mañci lōti yacainaṭaik koṭicci</l>
<l>kaṇpōṉ malartalu maritiva</l>
<l>ṭaṉpōṟ cāyaṉ maññaikku maritē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>Even for the waterlilies with unfurled mouths</l>
        <l>that flower</l>
        <l>in the fresh mountain pool</l>
        <l rend="space">on the slopes of the hill</l>
        <l>of the man from the hill-land,</l>
        <l rend="space">to bloom like the eyes</l>
        <l>of the creeper-like girl</l>
        <l>with pretty, fine hairs</l>
        <l>nd a swaying gait</l>
        <l>is difficult.</l>
        <l rend="space">Her grace is</l>
        <l>hard even for the peacocks</l>
        <l>to imitate.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
</text>
